"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-late-time-change-for-tatjana-smith-quest-for-gold-result-breaking-news\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 63, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9368663439643461, \"rank\": 0.06738659516331229, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbLate TIME CHANGE for Tatjana Smith's quest for gold  Organisers have confirmed a change in time for every race set to be contested on Monday, 29 July in the pool at the Paris La Defense Arena.\", \"from\": 65, \"to\": 396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 107, \"end\": 110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9368663439643461, \"rank\": 0.06738659516331229, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisershave confirmedachange in timefor every race set to be contested on Monday, 29 July in the pool at the Paris La Defense Arena.\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 533, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Enjoy the Paris Olympic Games 2024 experience at your favourite ATKV Resort!\", \"from\": 535, \"to\": 611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 599, \"end\": 603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ATKV\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ATKV\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ATKV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ATKV\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All eyes will be on South Africa'sTatjana Smithin the final of the women's 100m breaststroke.\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Originally the race was set to start at 21:25 (SA time), but now will start at21:34(SA time).\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 801, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, the final of the men's 100m backstroke in which South Africa'sPieter Coetzewill compete, will now start at21:27and not 21:19.\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 941, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All the changes in time can be found below.\", \"from\": 943, \"to\": 986, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile,Tatjana Smith(n\\u00e9e Schoenmaker) came into theParis Olympics 2024as the silver medallist from Tokyo in the 100m breaststroke and the gold medallist in the 200m.\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 1156, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1090, \"end\": 1095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9990749826690564, \"rank\": 0.000925796167453208, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Few would bet against hersurpassing her heroics there and taking gold-gold at these Games.\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1248, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She certainly laid down that marker by blazing her way to victory in both her heat and semi-final in the 100m at the Paris La Defense Arena on Sunday.\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Amazingly, she touched the wall in winningbothraces on the day in 1:05.00.\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1476, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How rare is that?\", \"from\": 1477, \"to\": 1494, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then again, the 27-year-old South African is a rare talent.\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1554, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith has always said that she takes races one at a time.\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1613, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She says that she swims as fast as she can and does not look at the time.\", \"from\": 1614, \"to\": 1687, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She says she ought to hold something back in the 100m because the 200m is her preferred event.\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1782, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, that does not look to be the case when you are watching from the stands.\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1864, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She is now a firm favourite to claim gold on Monday night.\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1924, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am just so grateful swimming to be good times again,\\\" the Team SA superstar said.\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 2010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1992, \"end\": 1994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.556470346361848e-24, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have not been close to my time from Tokyo (1:04.82), so to be swimming my best times since then is an amazing feeling.\", \"from\": 2012, \"to\": 2133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2051, \"end\": 2056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9990749826690564, \"rank\": 0.000925796167453208, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am just happy to be enjoying every race and it does not matter what times I do put up.\", \"from\": 2134, \"to\": 2222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's about the experience and how happy I am to be here doing what I am doing.\\\"\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2302, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The first semi-final of the evening was won by China's Qianting Tang in 1:05.83.\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2351, \"end\": 2356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999974348944464, \"rank\": 2.404263944913832e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2359, \"end\": 2372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tang_Qianting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Qianting Tang\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tang_Qianting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tang_Qianting\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was leading the world rankings in the event coming to Paris, with a time of 1:04.39, but she has not threatened that time in Paris and won the first semi-final, the slower of the two, in 1:05.83.\", \"from\": 2385, \"to\": 2584, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2443, \"end\": 2448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.219296531691965e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2514, \"end\": 2519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.219296531691965e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That places her fourth fastest heading into the final, with Mona McSharry (1:05.51) and Lily King (1:05.64) emerging as bigger threats to the South African.\", \"from\": 2585, \"to\": 2741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2645, \"end\": 2658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mona McSharry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\"}, {\"begin\": 2673, \"end\": 2682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lily_King\", \"score\": 0.999999999962256, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lily King\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lily_King\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lily_King\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith, racing as Tatjana Schoemaker in Tokyo three years ago, had then lowered the Olympic record to 1:04.82, also in the semi-finals.\", \"from\": 2743, \"to\": 2877, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2782, \"end\": 2787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9990749826690564, \"rank\": 0.000925796167453208, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That was without a crowd due to the Covid-19 restrictions.\", \"from\": 2878, \"to\": 2936, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here the crowd will have give her an extra gear and after that eye-popping morning heat of 1:05.00 she returned to the pool for the evening swim and mirrored that swim.\", \"from\": 2937, \"to\": 3105, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the heats she went out and turned in 30.57, before coming back to touch in 1:05.00.\", \"from\": 3107, \"to\": 3193, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the evening she went out and 30.63, before coming back to touch in 1:05.00.\", \"from\": 3195, \"to\": 3273, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So, marginally of course, she went out faster in the morning, but came home quicker in the evening.\", \"from\": 3274, \"to\": 3373, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Either way, it's gold medal form.\", \"from\": 3374, \"to\": 3407, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Leading South African bookmakersBetwayhave installed Smith as the9/20favourite to win the gold medal on Monday evening.\", \"from\": 3409, \"to\": 3528, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Qianting Tang is next best at17/5, followed by Lilly King(47/5)and Mona McSharry(19/2).\", \"from\": 3530, \"to\": 3617, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3530, \"end\": 3543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tang_Qianting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Qianting Tang\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tang_Qianting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tang_Qianting\"}, {\"begin\": 3597, \"end\": 3610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mona McSharry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Expect to hear Nkosi Sikelel' iAfrika once again ring out in France tonight.\", \"from\": 3619, \"to\": 3695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3634, \"end\": 3656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nkosi_Sikelel'_iAfrika\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nkosi Sikelel' iAfrika\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nkosi_Sikelel'_iAfrika\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nkosi_Sikelel'_iAfrika\"}, {\"begin\": 3634, \"end\": 3656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nkosi_Sikelel'_iAfrika\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nkosi Sikelel' iAfrika\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nkosi_Sikelel'_iAfrika\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nkosi_Sikelel'_iAfrika\"}, {\"begin\": 3680, \"end\": 3686, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_nat